<title>ITALY: Italy's Venice sees August CPI at 4.2 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Venice sees August CPI at 4.2 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>VENICE, Italy 1996-08-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Venice said its August consumer price index stood at 0.0 percent month-on-month and 4.2 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Venice's inflation rate was 0.0 percent and 4.7 percent respectively.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 7.89 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities which release preliminary inflation data have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.0    (0.0)     4.2  (4.7)</p>
<p>    Food				 -0.4   (-0.4)     5.2  (5.9)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.2)     5.1  (5.2)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.5   (-1.7)     2.5  (2.0)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.5    (0.0)     5.2  (5.9)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.4)     1.7  (1.5)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.2    (0.6)     3.3  (3.5)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture    -0.2   (-0.4)     1.9  (3.2)</p>
<p>    Education			  -0.4    (0.0)     5.2  (5.6)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	 -0.1    (1.0)     9.2  (9.3)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	-0.1    (0.1)     1.9  (2.3)</p>
